There's a modification necessary on Schema (`schema.dart`) to make it work.

Consider the following method `futureSchema`, heavily based on `Schema.createSchemaFromUrl`: 

```
Future<Schema>  futureSchema(String schemaUrl) async {

  if (true || uri.scheme == 'file' || uri.scheme == '') {
    return new io.File(uri.scheme == 'file' ? uri.toFilePath() : schemaUrl)
        .readAsString()
        .then((text) => Schema.createSchema(convert.json.decode(text)));
  } else {
    throw new Exception('Nonsense c: is a valid uri scheme: $schemaUrl');
  }
}
```
Then we can keep the `_validate` method even simpler. 
```
Future<bool> _validate(Object manifest) async {
  final String schemaPath = buildSchemaPath(fs);
  final Schema schema = await futureSchema(schemaPath);
  final Validator validator = new Validator(schema);
  . . .
```

So far I couldn't find any combination of File,`new Uri`, `fs.path`, `fs.file` or `'file:// + ???` that could build a path that can be acceptable to the current version of `createSchemaFromUrl`. `MemoryFileSystem` is ok with `C:\....\....yaml` but the current checks (`if (uri.scheme == 'file' || uri.scheme == '')`) prevent it from working.

